{"type":null,"faqId":41648,"title":"Does my phone support drawing letters when the screen is off to open applications?","answer":"<html>\n<head>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\n.p1{margin-left:1.18125in;margin-top:0.11111111in;margin-bottom:0.11111111in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.s1{font-weight:bold;}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"b1\">\n<div  >\n<p  >\n<span>When the screen is off, drawing letters can help you quickly open applications. Your phone supports using up to 4 letters to open applications.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>Go to </span><span class=\"s1\">Settings</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Motion control</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Draw</span><span>. Touch either the slide or draw letters preset options. Choose the application you would like to open. After checking the slide or draw letters check box, you can quickly open the applications by swiping on the screen or drawing the letter that corresponds to the application when the screen is off.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140243\" style=\"width:2.4090278in;height:4.2819443in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140244\" style=\"width:2.40625in;height:4.2819443in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":244,"languageName":"mm","faqCode":"7108","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1442207714000,"seriesProductName":"RIO-L01","visitedTimes":3,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":nul